{"questionId":"14617","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f(x) = 9 - {x^2}\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>9</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows part of the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/2f2c72d394c993dcd429caf8a596c3a7cd20e622.png\"></p>\n<p>Rectangle PQRS is drawn with P and Q on the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-axis and R and S on the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>Let OP = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider another function&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g(x) = {\\left( {x - 3} \\right)^2} + k\">\n  <mi>g</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that when the graphs of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"g\"> <mi>g</mi> </math></span> intersect,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2{x^2} - 6x + k = 0\"> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>6</mn> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f = g\"> <mi>f</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>g</mi> </math></span>,&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9 - {x^2} = {\\left( {x - 3} \\right)^2} + k\"> <mn>9</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>3</mn> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mi>k</mi> </math></span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>correct working&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp;</em>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9 - {x^2} = {x^2} - 6x + 9 + k\"> <mn>9</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>6</mn> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mn>9</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mi>k</mi> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9 - {x^2} - {x^2} + 6x - 9 - k = 0\"> <mn>9</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mn>6</mn> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>9</mn> <mo>−</mo> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2{x^2} - 6x + k = 0\"> <mn>2</mn> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>6</mn> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG&nbsp; N0</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14617","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ1.S_8d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that when the graphs of f and g intersect, 2 x 2 − 6 x + k = 0 .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}